{
  "name": "RPlog_Yavin_4_s_Trap",
  "title": "The Sphere in the Massassi Amphitheater",
  "summary": "Drawn by a premonition while on Tatooine, Luke Skywalker descends into a Massassi amphitheater on Yavin 4 and finds the young Force-sensitive Jessalyn collapsed on the stage, her hand clenched around a strange carved wooden sphere that has ensnared her mind in a dark mental trap. Reaching out through the Force, Luke anchors Jessalyn with his presence and calm, guiding her to fight her way back through the clinging shadows while prying the orb from her rigid fingers. As the sphere's tendrils briefly grasp at Luke too, he steadies them both and urges her not to try but to do, and Jessalyn finally wrenches free and opens her eyes. Shaken and exhausted, she explains she had simply wandered into the rainforest as she did in childhood and found the place and the artifact. Luke pockets the mystery, notes the strange writing on the sphere, and the two head back out as he reassures her, having come in answer to the letter she sent.",
